    stem: `A 40-year-old man presents to your practice with a mass in front of his left ear that he noted three months ago. On examination, the mass is painless, firm and mobile. When the patient is asked to smile, the left corner of his mouth does not elevate. Furthermore, trickling of saliva from the same side is noted. Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?`,
