    subtopic: "Central Retinal Artery Occlusion",
    stem: `A 52-year-old man presents to the emergency department with sudden-onset right-sided vision loss. His medical history is remarkable for the right-sided headache of 2 weeks duration, which is exacerbated by chewing. A fundoscopic exam is performed, and the findings are shown in the following photograph. Which of the following is the most likely cause of the visual loss?`,
