    topic: "Ophthalmology & ENT",
    subtopic: "Hyphema",
    stem: `A 38-year-old woman presents to the emergency department after getting hit in her right eye with a squash ball in a match. On examination, the visual acuity of the affected eye is decreased. The eye is shown in the accompanying photograph. Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?`,
