    id: "ent-amedex-0018",
    topic: "Ophthalmology & ENT",
    subtopic: "Neck mass evaluation and head and neck cancer",
    stem: `Jane, 65 years old, presents to your GP practice with a lump she noticed the other day above her left collar bone. She denies any symptoms. On examination, a 1.5x2 rubbery lump is felt in the left supraclavicular fossa which is none tender and mobile. There rest of the physical examination is inconclusive. Which one of the following is the next best step in management?`,
