    topic: "Ophthalmology & ENT",
    subtopic: "Sialadenitis and salivary duct calculi",
    stem: `A 75-year-old woman presents with a 16-hour history of a painful tender swelling under the right side of the jaw. The accompanying photograph shows the intraoral appearance. On examination, the swelling is exquisitely tender to palpation. Which one of the following would be the appropriate investigation to confirm the diagnosis?`,
