    stem: `A 48-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department with the complaint of sudden onset pain and tenderness that developed after he lifted an armchair at home for redecoration. On examination, restricted and painful movements of the lumbar area including flexion, extension, and rotation, as well as tenderness over the L4-L5 region is noted. Which one of the following is the most appropriate step in the initial management of this patient?`,
