    topic: "Orthopaedics",
    subtopic: "Low back pain - red flags",
    stem: `A 55-year-old man presents with sudden onset severe pain over the L4/L5 region which is sharp and shooting in nature and radiated down to both legs. He has never had such pain before and there is no history of preceding trauma or strain. He has lost six kilograms in the past two months. Which one of the following in history is the most important factor necessitating further investigations in this patient?`,
