    stem: `While gardening, a 45-year-old woman develops sudden onset low back pain. She is in the Emergency Department for evaluation now. Her past medical history is significant for breast cancer 10 years ago that was treated with breast-preserving surgery, adjuvant chemotherapy and radiotherapy. She has been disease-free since then. On examination, there is tenderness over the L4/L5 region, and painfully restricted flexion, extension and rotation. Neurological exam is unremarkable. Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?`,
