    topic: "Orthopaedics",
    subtopic: "Ankle Dislocation",
    stem: `While playing basketball, a 23-year-old man landed on his left foot awkwardly and injured his ankle. He is in the emergency department now. On examination, lateral dislocation of the ankle is evident. The dorsal pedis pulse is absent and the foot looks pale and cold to the touch. Which one of the following would be the next best step in management?`,
